<p>Source: Extracted from Plant Health (Fees) (England) Regulations (various – see below)</p><p>Schedule 2 of Regulations 2014 No. 601 sets out the reduced rates applicable to combinations of countries and products where, following risk assessments, reduced rates are charged. For example, the reduced rate inspection fees applicable to certain products from specific East African countries have also increased by around 236%. However, for some countries, the reduced rate charges have increased more substantially, for example for Ethiopian and Tanzanian roses.</p><p><b>Plant health inspection fees for roses from selected East African countries (£ per 20,000 stems)</b></p><table class="renderedtable" border="1" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0">
